    "created_at": "2016-03-07T14:33:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-07T14:33:28Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is entirely a consequence of the way [`Transforms`](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/0dcc51b3a395d06f5d77a0b9e9cdd2d875383217/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Transforms.cs#L131) works as a trait.\nThe [`Transform`](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/0dcc51b3a395d06f5d77a0b9e9cdd2d875383217/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Activities/Transform.cs#L81) activity creates a brand new actor.\n\nDiscussion from IRC:\n\n```\n[01:41:16]  <Phrohdoh> AMHOL: the engine creates a new actor when Transforms is used\n[01:41:49]  <AMHOL> Ahh OK, so no way to retain targets?\n[01:42:00]  <Phrohdoh> So from a gameplay perspective yes it is broken but the engine doesn't think so. We have DeployToUpgrade to somewhat resolve this, but there are valid cases for Transforms.\n[01:42:23]  <Phrohdoh> Correct, the new actor would have to alert the ones targeting the old one that it changed, and afaik we don't have anywhere to store that data.\n[01:42:26]  <Phrohdoh> (the list of attackers) \n```\n"
  },
